issue.title: Optimize error handling
issue.body:
Give the user better feedback what exactly did not work.
- No canteen detected
- No canteen matching

Maybe even ask for the wished one. Is there a session needed therefor?

Current behavior: If the skill can't detect a mensa, it simply triggers the help intent

issue.title: Which API to use?
issue.body:
I just started with using openmensa.org, but there might be some alternatives, mainly the API of the TUM Campus App (it's undocumented, check out the Android client for details: https://github.com/TCA-Team/TumCampusApp).

API related issues: #11, #1

issue.title: Which open mensa categories should be included?
issue.body:
Seems like there is not only a 'Tagesgericht X', 'Aktionsgericht X', but also eg. 'Biogericht X'. 

How to handle 'Aktion'? It is sometimes a real meal, but most of the time just a supplement.

Eg. https://openmensa.org/api/v2/canteens/139/days/2017-03-23/meals

issue.title: Crash when there are no meals at the requested day
issue.body:
Scenario:
- It's friday
- Say "Alexa, frage Mensa München 'was gibt es morgen zu essen'"?

API returns just nothing (nice design, openmensa 🙈):
https://openmensa.org/api/v2/canteens/139/days/2017-03-25/meals

The skill doesn't handle an empty response properly.

issue.title: Improve canteen custom slot
issue.body:
Currently there are only a couple of canteens in the custom slot type. 

- How does it behave if the user says "Mensa in Garching" instead of "Mensa Garching"? 
- Currently canteens are determined by string comparison. Should be improved.

issue.title: Support all Munich canteens
issue.body: Use a custom slot for all available canteens in Munich. Currently the canteen in Garching is hardcoded.

issue.title: Add support for StuCafe's
issue.body:
Alexa doesn't understand StuCafe and thinks its stuff like  "Stuck Kaffee".

Missing:
145 StuCafe Boltzmannstraße, Maschinenwesen
230 StuCafe Adalbertstraße
136 StuBistro Schellingstraße
232 StuCafe Karlstraße

Related #6
